data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression-tree building **won't compile** anymore. The new API accepts a regular lambda with imperative control flow:

```csharp
// EF Core 10 — just use a normal lambda
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Parameter` plumbing.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & full-path for nested

**Two changes:**

- **Sibling complex types** with same-named properties get a numeric suffix (`Street` → `Street1`) instead of silently sharing a column.
- **Nested complex types** now include the full path (`Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` → column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of `BillingAddress_City`).

If you have an existing database, **add explicit `HasColumnName` calls** to pin the old names and avoid a breaking migration:

```csharp
// Pin sibling properties to original shared column (if intentional)
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// Pin nested complex type to old (short) column name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
